/*
Problem- 1784. Check if Binary String has at most one segments of ones
Platform- Leetcode
Difficulty- Easy
Frequency- 0ms
Approach-Check if the string contains 01.
A segment of 1 means continuous 1s (like 1, 11, 111).
If 1 appears again after 0, it forms another segment.
Pattern 01 means:
first segment of 1 ended
new segment of 1 started.
So if 01 exists → more than one segment of 1 → return false.
If 01 does not exist → only one segment of 1 → return true.
Solution-*/
class Solution {
    public boolean checkOnesSegment(String s) {
        if(s.length()<3){
            int j=0;
           while(s.length()>j){
            if(s.charAt(j)=='1'){
                return true;
            }
            j++;
        }
            return false;
           }
        for(int i=1;s.length()>i;i++){
            if(s.charAt(i-1)=='0'&&s.charAt(i)=='1'){
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}
